      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The notion that you're being told to numb yourself is a common misconception. The medical community is genuinely concerned about your well-being, and a thorough evaluation by a licensed professional is the best way to identify any underlying issues. The pills and therapy are merely tools to help you cope with and manage your symptoms, not to control or silence you. In fact, many people have found that seeking help has been a liberating experience, allowing them to take control of their lives and make positive changes.",
