      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That sounds like the official script, though. I don't know. It just feels like if I go to them, I'm just handing over my autonomy to someone who's just gonna follow a manual. Like, they don't actually see *me*, they just see a diagnosis to be managed. Don't you think there's something inherently wrong with the idea that my actual feelings are just \"symptoms\" that need to be suppressed?",
